//- #1 (Initial setup of any html document)
//- doctype html tag
//- This will help identify the page as html just in case it needs to. 
//- The following renders to <!DOCTYPE html>
doctype html 


//- #2 (Initial setup of any html document)
//- html tag
//- Contents:
//-     This tag holds the whole html document
//-     The following renders to <html>...</html> 
html
   
    //- #3 
    //- (Initial setup of any html document)
    //- Add a head tag
    //- This tag holds your links of any type 
    //- Contents: 
    //-     Commonly you will see links to CSS files, 
    //-     JavaScript files, or third party services (Bootstrap, JQuery, Axios, etc)
    //-     The following renders to <head>...</head> -- Last traslation Should get the point. 
    head 
        title ðŸŽ“Grads
        meta(name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0")        
        //- #5 
        //- Linking the javascript and stylesheet from the public static folder
        link(rel="stylesheet", type="text/css", href="../styles.css")
        script(src="../../index.js" defer)
        
    //- #4 
    //- (Initial setup of any html document)
    //- Add a body tag
    //- Contents:
    //-     This will contain all of the elements 
    //-     that display & interact with the client.      
    body
